TITLE: Decrypting Encrypted String Data in Lit Protocol using JSX
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to decrypt previously encrypted string data using the Lit Protocol. It uses the decryptToString() function, passing in the necessary parameters including access control conditions, ciphertext, data hash, and session signatures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lit-protocol/docs/blob/main/docs/sdk/access-control/quick-start.md#2025-04-18_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
class Lit {
    ...

    async decrypt(ciphertext, dataToEncryptHash) {
      // Get the session signatures
      const sessionSigs = await this.getSessionSignatures();

      // Decrypt the message
      const decryptedString = await LitJsSdk.decryptToString(
        {
          accessControlConditions,
          chain: this.chain,
          ciphertext,
          dataToEncryptHash,
          sessionSigs,
        },
        this.litNodeClient,
      );

      // Return the decrypted string
      return { decryptedString };
    }

    ...
}
```

